{"lemma":"حَدِيثِ","slug":"حَدِيثِ","root":"ح.د.ث","root_slug":"ح-د-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-د-ث","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَدِيث","root":"حدث","pos":"N","occurrence_count":28},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7321","n7324"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AB%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"new"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"recent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"modern"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"recent event, fresh news"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"story, tale"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"talk, speech, discourse, conversation","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"وَمِنَ النّاسِ مَنْ يَشْتَرِي لَهْوَ الْحَدِيثِ لِيُضِلَّ عَنْ سَبِيلِ اللَّهِ بِغَيْرِ عِلْمٍ وَيَتَّخِذَهَا هُزُوًا أُولٰئِكَ لَهُمْ عَذَابٌ مُهِينٌ","english":"And of the people is he who buys the amusement of speech to mislead [others] from the way of Allah without knowledge and who takes it in ridicule. Those will have a humiliating punishment."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a hadith","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"The entire body of hadiths","tags":["uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"ثمّ سألته – تعالى جدّه – أن يهديني إلى عمل وثيق الصِّلة بالقرآن الكريم والحديث الشَّريف، وقد كان لي ما تمنّيت – فالحمد لله على ما أنعم أوّلًا وآخرًا – إذ هداني إلى دراسة كتب جمعت في أثنائها شرح الألفاظ الغريبة الواردة في القرآن والحديث، فكان عنوان أُطروحتي […]"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح د ث (ḥ d ṯ). Related to Hebrew חָדָשׁ (khadásh, ḥāḏāš) and Amharic አዲስ (ʾäddis), Ugaritic 𐎈𐎄𐎘 (ḥdṯ) and Aramaic חֲדַת (ḥăḏaṯ)."},"ipa":["/ħa.diːθ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7321","headword_ar":"حَدِيثٌ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"New, recent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadiymN","text_ar":"قَدِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having had, a beginning; existing newly, for the first time, not having been before;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdivN","text_ar":"حَادِثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought into existence, caused to be, made, produced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done, newly, for the first time, not having been before; begun,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originated; invented; innovated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHodavN","text_ar":"مُحْدَثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last two sentences, in four places. And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HidovaAnN","text_ar":"حِدْثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hadiyvu EahodK biAlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"هُوَ حَدِيثُ عَهْدٍ بِالاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was, recently become a Muslim."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyvuw","text_ar":"حَدِيثُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EahodK bikuforihimo","text_ar":"عَهْدٍ بِكُفْرِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAljaAhiliy~api","text_ar":"بِالجَاهِلِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN Eahoduhumo","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ عَهْدُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) Men"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lately in their state of infidelity"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the state of paganism"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignorance"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who have but recently ceased to be in their state of infidelity"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Information; a piece of information; intelligence; an announcement; news,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tidings; a piece of news; an account; a narration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrative; a story;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (S, K;) employed to signify little and much; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hid~iyvaY","text_ar":"حِدِّيثَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"matter, that is talked of, told,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrated, and transmitted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHoduwvapN","text_ar":"اُحْدُوثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is talked of, told,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wonderful thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, TA:) it has been asserted, says MF, that there is no difference between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHdwvp","text_ar":"احدوثة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv","text_ar":"حديث"},{"kind":"text","text":"in usage, and in denoting"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is good"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in contradiction to such as say that the former peculiarly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of story"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which there is no profit nor any truth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as amatory stories, and the like fictions of the Arabs: Fr asserts it to signify peculiarly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a laughable and an absurd story;"},{"kind":"text","text":"differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv","text_ar":"حديث"},{"kind":"text","text":": and Ibn-Hishám El-Lakhmee, in his Expos of the Fs, says that it is only used to denote"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Lb replies against him, in his Expos., that it is sometimes used to denote"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in a saying mentioned by Yaakoob, which see below: (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAdiyvu","text_ar":"اَحَادِيثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", contr. to analogy, (S, K,) said by Fr to be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHoduwvapN","text_ar":"اُحْدُوثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then used as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv","text_ar":"حديث"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) but IB says that this is not the case; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HidovaAnN","text_ar":"حِدْثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudovaAnN","text_ar":"حُدْثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv","text_ar":"حديث"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) sometimes occurring; the latter, rare. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEotu HadiyvFA HasanFA","text_ar":"سَمِعْتُ حَدِيثًا حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanapF","text_ar":"حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hid~iyvaY","text_ar":"حِدِّيثَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I heard a good story"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrative"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; both meaning the same. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainota$ara","text_ar":"اِنْتَشَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanapN","text_ar":"حَسَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu fiY Aln~aAsi A^uHoduwvapN","text_ar":"لَهُ فِى النَّاسِ اُحْدُوثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good story of him became spread abroad among the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a saying mentioned by Yaakoob in his “ Isláh. ” (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maliyHapN","text_ar":"مَلِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^vHoduwvapN","text_ar":"اثحْدُوثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pretty story"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAdiyvu milaAHN","text_ar":"اَحَادِيثُ مِلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pretty stories"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado SaAra fulaAnN A^aHoduwvapF","text_ar":"قَدْ صَارَ فُلَانٌ اَحْدُوثَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has become the subject of a story,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a wonderful story:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, as is said in the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAruwA A^aHaAdiyva","text_ar":"صَارُوا اَحَادِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": there said to be tropical]. (IB, TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyv","text_ar":"حَدِيث"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Apostle of God: (Msb:) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narration of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHad~iv","text_ar":"مُحَدِّث"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) [meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabawiY~N","text_ar":"نَبَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tradition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narration, relating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"describing, a saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action &c. of Mo- hammad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] this word and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tradition that is traced up to Mohammad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a Sahábee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a Tábi'ee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqA^","text_ar":"رقا"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv","text_ar":"حديث"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what comes from the Prophet:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to what comes from another than the Prophet; or from him or another: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avarN","text_ar":"اَثَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to what comes from a Companion of the Prophet; but it may also be applied to a saying of the Prophet: (Kull p. 152:) the word in this sense, i. e. the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv","text_ar":"حديث"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Prophet, has for its pl. only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAdiyvu","text_ar":"اَحَادِيثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and therefore Sb mentions it in the category of those words which have pls. anomalously formed; such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwDN","text_ar":"عَرُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaAriyDu","text_ar":"اَعَارِيضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilN","text_ar":"بَاطِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaATiylu","text_ar":"اَبَاطِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadiyva","text_ar":"الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"written at the end of a quotation of a part of a trad. is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiqoraA^i AlHadiyva","text_ar":"اِقْرَاِ الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Read the tradition."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN qudosiY~N","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ قُدْسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A holy tradition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narration"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what God has told to his prophet by inspiration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a dream,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in sleep, and the prophet has told in his own phraseology:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the Kur-án is esteemed above this, because [it is held that] its words also were revealed: (KT:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of which the words are from the apostle, but the meaning is from God, by inspiration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a dream,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 288.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","Mgh","K","IB","L","KT"]},{"entry_id":"n7324","headword_ar":"حِدِّيثٌ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HidovN","text_ar":"حِدْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}